ALPHABETIC INDEX OF

3,071 GRAVESTONES

FOUND 2000-2001 AT

WALNUT RIDGE CEMETERY, JEFFERSONVILLE, INDIANA

Abstracted by Jeanne Burke <jeanne_b@hotmail.com>

Â© 2001

A SMALL PORTION OF WALNUT RIDGE CEMETERY NOTICE: This is an alphabetic index of 3,071 of the GRAVESTONES found at Walnut Ridge Cemetery in Jeffersonville, Clark County, Indiana. The earliest death date abstracted below is 1817; the most recent is 1986.

This gravestone index includes only Sections A-K, the oldest part of the cemetery on the I-65 side of Hamburg Pike.

The information below was personally abstracted by Jeanne Burke of Charlestown, Indiana. She spent many months, in all kinds of weather, largely on her hands and knees, transcribing thousands of stones found at Walnut Ridge.

Jeanne has given us permission to share this information with you.

This is NOT an index based on the decades of records of burials at Walnut Ridge Cemetery. It is a list of all burials memorialized by stones visible in 2000-2001. It obviously does not include any stones which have sunk below the surface of the earth, stones which have been destroyed, stones which have stolen or stones that never existed.

If you are looking for someone believed to be buried at Walnut Ridge and cannot find his/her name below either (1) the grave was not marked with a permanent (i.e., stone) marker OR (2) the stone is destroyed, illegible or otherwise not available for transcription.

If it were sold in printed form, the cost would be astronomical and the shipping would be exhorbitant. BUT, you can purchase the full index with all the additional information mentioned above from Jeanne for only $15 (including shipping and handling). She will mail it to you on a CD-ROM, on which the index will be published in Adobe Acrobat PDF format. The Adobe Acrobat Reader program necessary to view PDF files will be included on the CD-ROM.

If you are interested in purchasing the full, detailed index, please write to Jeanne Burke at jeanne_b@hotmail.com.
